Vice President Mike Pence wrote an op-ed in which he highlights the economic progress made under President Donald Trump's leadership. Pence emphasizes that businesses have created 7 million American jobs since Trump's election and wages are rising at the fastest pace in 10 years. He also mentions the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), which he says is the largest trade deal in American history. Pence believes that the USMCA will add $235 billion in economic growth and 589,000 jobs to the US economy. He asserts that the USMCA will benefit Americans of all political parties and backgrounds and calls on Congress to pass the agreement.